snippet: Catherine, the Duchess of Cambridge, joined Chirlane McCray, the wife of Mayor Bill de Blasio, in a visit to the Northside Center for Child Development on East 110th Street.
abstract: Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge, and New York City's first lady Chirlane McCray visit Northside Center for Child Development in Harlem, where they help wrap holiday gifts; rest of days events scheduled for the royals include lunch at British consul general's residence and courtside seats at the Barclay's Center in Brooklyn for a game between the Nets and Cleveland Cavaliers.
lead_paragraph: Catherine, the Duchess of Cambridge, joined Chirlane McCray, the wife of Mayor Bill de Blasio, in a visit to the Northside Center for Child Development on East 110th Street.
